# QA Automation Framework - Claude Code Context

## Project Structure
This is a pytest + Playwright test automation framework for Michigan ORS applications (ESS, WSS, MIORS, CLT, Clarety).

## Framework Pattern
- Tests are registered with `@register_test("test_name")` decorator from `lib/test_registry.py`
- Test data comes from Excel RunManager.xlsx via `lib/test_data_manager.py`
- Each test receives an `Application` object with `.ui`, `.api`, `.db` layers
- Page objects live in `application/ui/` (e.g., `ess_login_page.py`)
- Locators live in `application/ui/` (e.g., `ess_page_locators.py`)
- Tests are organized by app: `tests/ess/`, `tests/wss/`, `tests/miors/`, etc.

## How to Write a New Test
```python
from lib.test_registry import register_test
from application.application import Application

@register_test("test_my_new_test")
def test_my_new_test(app: Application):
    app.ui.launch_ESSUrl(app.env["base_url"])
    app.ui.login_page.loginESS(app.data, app.sheet_name)
    # ... test steps ...
```

## Locator Pattern
```python
class ESSPageLocators:
    SOME_BUTTON = "css=input[type='submit'][value='Submit']"
    SOME_LINK = "text=Work on Reports"
    SOME_TABLE = "css=table.dataTable"
```

## Key Files
- `conftest.py` - Fixtures, browser setup, test parametrization
- `lib/constants.py` - URLs, credentials, file paths
- `lib/test_data_manager.py` - Excel read/write operations
- `lib/actions.py` - Common helper functions
- `application/application.py` - Main Application facade

## Running Tests
```
pytest tests/test_run_manager.py --env=uat25 --mode=uat
pytest tests/test_run_manager.py --env=prod --mode=prod
```

## When Generating Locators
- Prefer CSS selectors over XPath for simple cases
- Use `text=` for link/button text matching
- Use `css=` prefix for CSS selectors
- For tables, use nth-child or :has-text() pseudo-selectors
- The app is Struts-based, so IDs may contain dynamic prefixes
